1.text: Find a flat, stable and safe place to change your tire.

2.text: Apply the parking brake and put car into "Park" position.

4.text: Take out the spare tire and the jack.

5.text: Raise the jack until it is supporting (but not lifting) the car.

6.text: Remove the hubcap and loosen the nuts by turning counterclockwise.

7.text: Pump or crank the jack to lift the tire off the ground.

8.text: Remove the nuts the rest of the way.

10.text: Place the spare tire on the hub.

11.text: Tighten the nuts by hand until they are all snug.

12.text: Lower the car without applying full weight on the tire.

13.text: Lower the car to the ground fully and remove the jack.

14.text: Put the old tire in your trunk and take it to a mechanic.
